UTFString.name: UTFString
UTFString.description: An octet string containing administrative information, preferably in human-readable form. To facilitate internationalization, this information is represented using the ISO/IEC IS 10646-1 character set, encoded as an octet string using the UTF-8 transformation format described in [RFC2279]. Since additional code points are added by amendments to the 10646 standard from time to time, implementations must be prepared to encounter any code point from 0x00000000 to 0x7fffffff. Byte sequences that do not correspond to the valid UTF-8 encoding of a code point or are outside this range are prohibited. The use of control codes should be avoided. When it is necessary to represent a newline, the control code sequence CR LF should be used. The use of leading or trailing white space should be avoided. For code points not directly supported by user interface hardware or software, an alternative means of entry and display, such as hexadecimal, may be provided. For information encoded in 7-bit US-ASCII, the UTF-8 encoding is identical to the US-ASCII encoding. UTF-8 may require multiple bytes to represent a single character / code point; thus the length of this object in octets may be different from the number of characters encoded. Similarly, size constraints refer to the number of encoded octets, not the number of characters represented by an encoding. Note that when this TC is used for an object that is used or envisioned to be used as an index, then a SIZE restriction MUST be specified so that the number of sub-identifiers for any object instance does not exceed the limit of 128, as defined by [RFC1905]. Note that the size of an SnmpAdminString object is measured in octets, not characters.

AdminAccountPrivilegeType.name: AdminAccountPrivilegeType
AdminAccountPrivilegeType.description: This field specifies the privilege level of the account. The default is global-admin. global-admin grants full access to the administrator. pool-admin designates the administrator to have access only to one or more pools, and does not have access to global and group-level administrator. volume-admin designates the administrator to have access to specific volumes within specific storage pools.

AdminAccountType.name: AdminAccountType
AdminAccountType.description: This field specifies the type of account. The read-write account type allows the user to modify any group settings. The read-only account allows only read-only access to group configuration data. The default is read-write. Changing this value will come into affect only for new login of the user. Currently logged in sessions will not be affected. Read-only account is only applicable for group admin accounts/pool-admin accounts. Group-admins with read-only set cannot modify any settings.

eqlStorageGroupEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupEntry
eqlStorageGroupEntry.description: An entry (row) containing storage group information.

eqlGroupId.name: eqlGroupId
eqlGroupId.description: This index uniquely identifies the group. This index should always be 1.

eqlGroupIsSingleSubnet.name: eqlGroupIsSingleSubnet
eqlGroupIsSingleSubnet.description: This field is used to indicate whether or not all the arrays within a group are located in the same subset. The default is single-subnet.

eqlGroupDefaultRoutingProtocol.name: eqlGroupDefaultRoutingProtocol
eqlGroupDefaultRoutingProtocol.description: This field is used to indicate the routing protocol use when a group spans multiple subnets. The support protocols are RIP and OFPS. The default value is none.

eqlGroupIsStorageOptimization.name: eqlGroupIsStorageOptimization
eqlGroupIsStorageOptimization.description: This field is used to indicate whether the Storage Pool is optimized for capacity (RAID 5/50) or performance (RAID 10). The default is capacity.

eqlGroupDiskAddWaitTime.name: eqlGroupDiskAddWaitTime
eqlGroupDiskAddWaitTime.description: This field is used to indicated how long to wait in minutes before including newly inserted drives into the RAID set. The delay allows for multiple drives to be inserted before the expansion begins. The default is 2 minutes.

eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotSize.name: eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotSize
eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotSize.description: This field is used to specify by default what percentage of a volume is reserved for SnapShots. The default is 100%. It can be overriden on a per volume basis. If a volume, testvol, is 100MB, and the GroupDefaultSnapshotsize is 100%, than 100MB will reserved for SnapShots of testvol.

eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotWarningLevel.name: eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotWarningLevel
eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotWarningLevel.description: This field is used to specify by default when the administrator is warned that the space used for SnapShots close to being exhausted. The default is 20%. It can be overriden on a per volume basis.

eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotDeletePolicy.name: eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotDeletePolicy
eqlGroupDefaultSnapshotDeletePolicy.description: This field specifies what should happen when the space reserved for SnapShots is exhuasted. The default is delete-oldest SnapShot.

eqlGroupLogLevel.name: eqlGroupLogLevel
eqlGroupLogLevel.description: This field specifies the loglevel for the group. The log level determines which messages are written to the console. The following levels are supported. The value of this object will be an OR of the values associated with each level. LEVEL VALUE ------- ------- INFO 0x04 WARNING 0x08 ERROR 0x10 FATAL 0x20 DIAG 0x40 AUDIT 0x80 Default value is INFO|WARNING|ERROR|FATAL = 0x04|0x08|0x10|0x20| = 0x3c = 60

eqlGroupDescription.name: eqlGroupDescription
eqlGroupDescription.description: This field contains a use supplied description for the group. There is no default.

eqlGroupIscsiNamePrefix.name: eqlGroupIscsiNamePrefix
eqlGroupIscsiNamePrefix.description: This field specifies the prefix for the iSCSI target names. The default is iqn.2001-04.com.equallogic. This can be overriden on a per volume basis. However the name must conform to the iSCSI Specification.

eqlGroupDefaultAliasToVolumeName.name: eqlGroupDefaultAliasToVolumeName
eqlGroupDefaultAliasToVolumeName.description: This field specifies whether or not to default the iSCSI alias to the name of the volume. This can be overriden on a per volume basis. The default is to set the iSCSI alias to the volume name.

eqlGroupEmailSrcDomain.name: eqlGroupEmailSrcDomain
eqlGroupEmailSrcDomain.description: This field specifies the SNMP domain name used in the FROM email address in generated email. e.g., everything after @ in foo@equallogic.com .

eqlGroupName.name: eqlGroupName
eqlGroupName.description: This field specifies the Well Known Name for the group. It must be a name which is resolvable by DNS. There is no default for Group Name.

eqlGroupIpAddr.name: eqlGroupIpAddr
eqlGroupIpAddr.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupEnableWebAccessSSL.name: eqlGroupEnableWebAccessSSL
eqlGroupEnableWebAccessSSL.description: This field specifies whether or not to allow web access to the group using https. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupEnableWebAccessUnsecure.name: eqlGroupEnableWebAccessUnsecure
eqlGroupEnableWebAccessUnsecure.description: This field specifies whether or not to allow web access to the group using http. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupEnableCliAccessSSH.name: eqlGroupEnableCliAccessSSH
eqlGroupEnableCliAccessSSH.description: This field specifies whether or not to allow ssh access to the group. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupEnableCliAccessUnsecure.name: eqlGroupEnableCliAccessUnsecure
eqlGroupEnableCliAccessUnsecure.description: This field specifies whether or not to allow telnet access to the group. The default is FALSE.

eqlGroupEnableEmailNotifications.name: eqlGroupEnableEmailNotifications
eqlGroupEnableEmailNotifications.description: This field is used to specify whether to notify administrators on alarms via email. The default is FALSE.

eqlGroupEnableSNMPTraps.name: eqlGroupEnableSNMPTraps
eqlGroupEnableSNMPTraps.description: This field is used to specify whether to notify administrators on alarms via SNMP TRAPS. The default is FALSE.

eqlGroupEnableSyslog.name: eqlGroupEnableSyslog
eqlGroupEnableSyslog.description: This field is used to specify whether to notify administrators on alarms via syslog. The default is FALSE.

eqlGroupEmailPriorityMask.name: eqlGroupEmailPriorityMask
eqlGroupEmailPriorityMask.description: This field is used to configure the type of events to be sent in email notifications. The following type of events are supported. info(4), warning(8), error(16), fatal(32) More than one type of event can be specified by adding the correspodning values. Ex: To specify warning,error,fatal the value can be set to 8+16+32 = 56. Setting this field to zero results in sending no events using email notification.

eqlGroupSNMPPriorityMask.name: eqlGroupSNMPPriorityMask
eqlGroupSNMPPriorityMask.description: This field is currently not being used.

eqlGroupSysLogPriorityMask.name: eqlGroupSysLogPriorityMask
eqlGroupSysLogPriorityMask.description: This field is used to configure the type of events to be sent in syslog notifications. The following type of events are supported. info(4), warning(8), error(16), fatal(32) More than one type of event can be specified by adding the correspodning values. Ex: To specify warning,error,fatal the value can be set to 8+16+32 = 56. Setting this field to zero results in sending no events using syslog notification.

eqlGroupDefaultSite.name: eqlGroupDefaultSite
eqlGroupDefaultSite.description: This field specifies the site where the volume resides. Sites are defined on a per array basis. Sites are used to define where primary and secondary copies of volume mirror reside. The default is the default site. This means that the location of the volume is unrestricted.

eqlGroupPasswd1.name: eqlGroupPasswd1
eqlGroupPasswd1.description: An octet string containing the password to authenticate members joining the group. If written, it changes the password for the account. If read, it returns a zero-length string.

eqlGroupObjectReuseScrub.name: eqlGroupObjectReuseScrub
eqlGroupObjectReuseScrub.description: If enabled, an object is zeroed out before reuse so that the new entity using the object will not be aware of the old contents of the object. This field is deprecated and is unsupported from 7.0.

eqlGroupEnableSSH.name: eqlGroupEnableSSH
eqlGroupEnableSSH.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupEnableTelnet.name: eqlGroupEnableTelnet
eqlGroupEnableTelnet.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupEnableFTP.name: eqlGroupEnableFTP
eqlGroupEnableFTP.description: This field specifies whether or not to allow ftp access to the group. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupEmailSrcUserName.name: eqlGroupEmailSrcUserName
eqlGroupEmailSrcUserName.description: This field specifies user portion of the FROM email address used in generated email. e.g., everything before @ in foo@equallogic.com .

eqlGroupSyslogFacility.name: eqlGroupSyslogFacility
eqlGroupSyslogFacility.description: This field specifies the facility code which you would like applied to all eqllog messages that are targeted at syslog.

eqlGroupEnableCLB.name: eqlGroupEnableCLB
eqlGroupEnableCLB.description: This field specifies whether or not to turn on Connection Load balancer. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupEnableVolBal.name: eqlGroupEnableVolBal
eqlGroupEnableVolBal.description: This field specifies whether or not to turn on volume balancing. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupDiscoveryFilter.name: eqlGroupDiscoveryFilter
eqlGroupDiscoveryFilter.description: If set to true, the list of volumes returned during discovery is filtered based on chap configuration in volume ACLs. The default is FALSE.

eqlGroupEmailSupportContact.name: eqlGroupEmailSupportContact
eqlGroupEmailSupportContact.description: This field specifies the customer email address for support to contact in the event of a system failure. Configuring this field will enable each member to send an e-mail to this address and customer support in the event of a critical hardware failure.

eqlGroupReplicationWindowSize.name: eqlGroupReplicationWindowSize
eqlGroupReplicationWindowSize.description: This field specifies the receiving window size of the tcp connection established to secondary site during replication data transfer. Minimum value is 72KB.Maximum value is 2048KB.

eqlGroupConfigurationFlags.name: eqlGroupConfigurationFlags
eqlGroupConfigurationFlags.description: This field defines the common place holder for group wide configuration flag. The flags must be of type enable(1) or disable(0). and the default value will always be disable(0).

eqlGroupISCSIPortalGrpTag.name: eqlGroupISCSIPortalGrpTag
eqlGroupISCSIPortalGrpTag.description: A flag used internally by the iSCSI subsystem to determine the upgrade history of this storage group and infer the default iSCSI Target Portal Group ID. This value is changed internally by the group management daemon as members are added or upgraded such that the value is non zero if any group member has been previously configured with firmware prior to 2.3.6

eqlGroupMaxConcurrentReplicas.name: eqlGroupMaxConcurrentReplicas
eqlGroupMaxConcurrentReplicas.description: This field specifies the maximum number of replications that are transferring data at one time. The minimum value is 1, the maximum value is 16, and the default value is 16.

eqlGroupDefaultThinWarn.name: eqlGroupDefaultThinWarn
eqlGroupDefaultThinWarn.description: The default eqliscsiVolumeThinWarnPercentage value used when creating thin provisoned volumes.

eqlGroupDefaultThinMaxGrow.name: eqlGroupDefaultThinMaxGrow
eqlGroupDefaultThinMaxGrow.description: The default eqliscsiVolumeThinMaxGrowPercentage value used when creating thin provisoned volumes.

eqlGroupDefaultMgmtGatewayIpAddressType.name: eqlGroupDefaultMgmtGatewayIpAddressType
eqlGroupDefaultMgmtGatewayIpAddressType.description: This field is used to indicate the default gateway for the management network. This field contains the address of the local router used to forward network traffic beyond the local management subnet. Gateways are used to connect multiple subnets. There is no default value for this entry.

eqlGroupDefaultMgmtGatewayIpAddress.name: eqlGroupDefaultMgmtGatewayIpAddress
eqlGroupDefaultMgmtGatewayIpAddress.description: This field is used to indicate the default gateway for the management network. This field contains the address of the local router used to forward network traffic beyond the local management subnet. Gateways are used to connect multiple subnets. There is no default value for this entry.

eqlGroupInet6AddrType.name: eqlGroupInet6AddrType
eqlGroupInet6AddrType.description: This field specifies the type of the IPv6 Well Known Address for the group. This is the IPv6 address iSCSI Initiators will used to connect to the group.

eqlGroupInet6Addr.name: eqlGroupInet6Addr
eqlGroupInet6Addr.description: This field specifies the IPv6 Well Known Address for the group. This is the IPv6 address iSCSI Initiators will used to connect to the group. There is no default value for this field.

eqlGroupInetAddrType.name: eqlGroupInetAddrType
eqlGroupInetAddrType.description: This field specifies the type of the IPv4 Well Known Address for the group. This is the IPv4 address iSCSI Initiators will used to connect to the group.

eqlGroupInetAddr.name: eqlGroupInetAddr
eqlGroupInetAddr.description: This field specifies the IPv4 Well Known Address for the group. This is the IPv4 address iSCSI Initiators will used to connect to the group. There is no default value for this field.

eqlGroupSupportSlowSwitch.name: eqlGroupSupportSlowSwitch
eqlGroupSupportSlowSwitch.description: This field is used to indicate the slow switch support for the group.

eqlGroupProfileIndex.name: eqlGroupProfileIndex
eqlGroupProfileIndex.description: This field represents the profile identifier.

eqlGroupEnableSSHProtocolV1.name: eqlGroupEnableSSHProtocolV1
eqlGroupEnableSSHProtocolV1.description: This field specifies whether or not the SSH service should support the V1 Protocol. The default is TRUE.

eqlGroupEnableStandbyButton.name: eqlGroupEnableStandbyButton
eqlGroupEnableStandbyButton.description: This field specifies if the standby button on the Pirates/Porfidio enclosures will be enabled/disabled. The default is FALSE.

eqlGroupLDAPLoginAuthEnable.name: eqlGroupLDAPLoginAuthEnable
eqlGroupLDAPLoginAuthEnable.description: This field enables LDAP login authentication.

eqlGroupDefaultDcbVlanId.name: eqlGroupDefaultDcbVlanId
eqlGroupDefaultDcbVlanId.description: Default VLAN ID for DCB control packets on interfaces.

eqlGroupThermalShutdownOverride.name: eqlGroupThermalShutdownOverride
eqlGroupThermalShutdownOverride.description: This field specifies whether thermal shutdownn override is enabled or disabled.

eqlGroupEnableLegacyCryptos.name: eqlGroupEnableLegacyCryptos
eqlGroupEnableLegacyCryptos.description: This field specifies whether legacy crypto protocols should be enabled or not. This affects what protocols should be supported by applications such as SSH server, HTTPS server, LDAP client, SNMPv3 agent, etc.

eqlGroupMaxReplSegments.name: eqlGroupMaxReplSegments
eqlGroupMaxReplSegments.description: This field specifies the maximum number of replica segments of 256K size per volume that are transferring data at one time. The minimum value is 1, the maximum value is 60, and the default value is 60.

eqlGroupEnableVolumeRecovery.name: eqlGroupEnableVolumeRecovery
eqlGroupEnableVolumeRecovery.description: This field specifies whether or not the recoverable volume feature is enabled. The default value is enabled.

eqlGroupSessionIdleTimeout.name: eqlGroupSessionIdleTimeout
eqlGroupSessionIdleTimeout.description: This is the number of minutes a session may remain idle before being logged out for inactivty. The maximum timeout value is 24 hours or 1440 minutes. The minimum value is 1 minute. The default value is 30 minutes.

eqlGroupSessionIdleTimeoutEnable.name: eqlGroupSessionIdleTimeoutEnable
eqlGroupSessionIdleTimeoutEnable.description: Enable/disable the idle session timeout feature. The default is disabled.

eqlGroupSessionBannerEnable.name: eqlGroupSessionBannerEnable
eqlGroupSessionBannerEnable.description: Enable/disable the session banner feature. The default is disabled.

eqlGroupDefaultVolSnapshotBorrowEnabled.name: eqlGroupDefaultVolSnapshotBorrowEnabled
eqlGroupDefaultVolSnapshotBorrowEnabled.description: This field allows the user a way to change the default behavior of snapshot borrowing on new volume creates across the group.

eqlGroupRecoveryLifeTimeEnable.name: eqlGroupRecoveryLifeTimeEnable
eqlGroupRecoveryLifeTimeEnable.description: This field enables or disables the lifetime that a deleted volume can remain in the recovery bin. When enabled, a volume will be permanently deleted after the recovery lifetime in the recovery bin.

eqlGroupRecoveryLifeTime.name: eqlGroupRecoveryLifeTime
eqlGroupRecoveryLifeTime.description: This field defines the amount of time (in seconds) that a deleted volume can remain in the recovery bin before being permanently deleted by the system. The default value (0) is one week.

eqlGroupTimeProtocol.name: eqlGroupTimeProtocol
eqlGroupTimeProtocol.description: This field specifies the active network time protocol. The value may be ntp(0) or sntp(1) with a default value of ntp(0).

eqlGroupRecoveryTrimmerFreq.name: eqlGroupRecoveryTrimmerFreq
eqlGroupRecoveryTrimmerFreq.description: This field defines the frequency (in seconds) that the system will scan for volumes that have been in the recovery bin past their lifetime. The default value is one scan every 24 hours.

eqlGroupUpdateLast.name: eqlGroupUpdateLast
eqlGroupUpdateLast.description: The time of last update performed represented as the number of seconds since the epoch.

eqlGroupDefaultSectorSize.name: eqlGroupDefaultSectorSize
eqlGroupDefaultSectorSize.description: This field specifies, in bytes, the default volume sector size for this group.

eqlGroupCompressionScanFreq.name: eqlGroupCompressionScanFreq
eqlGroupCompressionScanFreq.description: This index is the last assigned index value associated with VVol Volumes.

eqlGroupMonitorReminderTimestamp.name: eqlGroupMonitorReminderTimestamp
eqlGroupMonitorReminderTimestamp.description: UTC timestamp when to display the monitoring connection reminder. 0 to display immediately. 0x7fffffff to never display.

eqlStorageGroupStatusEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusEntry
eqlStorageGroupStatusEntry.description: An entry (row) containing Group status information.

eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpace.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpace
eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpace.description: This field specifies the total size of the Storage Pool in MBs.

eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceUsed.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceUsed
eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceUsed.description: This field specifies the total space reserved for volume data within the Storage Pool in MBs. Note that this value does not include space reserved for snapshots or replication.

eqlStorageGroupStatusTotalMembersOnLine.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusTotalMembersOnLine
eqlStorageGroupStatusTotalMembersOnLine.description: This field specifies the number of group members which are online.

eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceReserved.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceReserved
eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceReserved.description: This field specifies the total space reserved for SnapShot data within the Storage Pool in MBs.

eqlStorageGroupStatusReservedSpaceInUse.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusReservedSpaceInUse
eqlStorageGroupStatusReservedSpaceInUse.description: This field specifies the total reserved space in use by snapshots in the storage pool . This will be equal to sum of eqlMemberSnapStorage for all members.

eqlStorageGroupStatusDateAndTime.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusDateAndTime
eqlStorageGroupStatusDateAndTime.description: This field specifies the current time in group represented as number of seconds since epoch.

eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotsInUse.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotsInUse
eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotsInUse.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshots within the group that currently have active iSCSI connections.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumesInUse.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumesInUse
eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumesInUse.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshotsvolumes within the group that currently have active iSCSI connections.

eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotsOnline.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotsOnline
eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotsOnline.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshots available for iSCSI connections.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumesOnline.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumesOnline
eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumesOnline.description: This field specifies the total number of volumes available for iSCSI connections.

eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotCount.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapshotCount.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshots in this group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeCount.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeCount.description: This field specifies the total number of volumes in this group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusMemberCount.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusMemberCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusMemberCount.description: This field specifies the total number of members in this group irrelevant of current member state.

eqlStorageGroupStatusMembersInUse.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusMembersInUse
eqlStorageGroupStatusMembersInUse.description: This field specifies the total number of online+offline members in this group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusFreeSpace.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusFreeSpace
eqlStorageGroupStatusFreeSpace.description: This field specifies the total free space of the Storage Pool in Mega Bytes.

eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceDelegated.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceDelegated
eqlStorageGroupStatusPoolSpaceDelegated.description: This field specifies the amount of free space of the Storage Pool which has been partitioned for use by external services such as remote replication. This space is reserved and can be controlled by the users of these services. This sum represents total space reserved by all of the entries in the replicant site table

eqlStorageGroupStatusDelegatedUsedSpace.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusDelegatedUsedSpace
eqlStorageGroupStatusDelegatedUsedSpace.description: This field specifies the amount of space used by external services such as remote replication. This sum represents total space used by all of the entries in the replicant site table

eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveSpace.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveSpace
eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveSpace.description: This sum represents total space reserved for all volumes for replication purposes.

eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveInUse.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveInUse
eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveInUse.description: This sum represents total space in use for all volumes for replication purposes. This value will be equal to sum of eqlMemberReplStorage for all members.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeSpaceSubscrib.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeSpaceSubscribed
eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeSpaceSubscrib.description: This field specifies the total subscribed space for all volumes in the group. For a thin provisioned volume, subscribed space is the advertised space. For a regular volume, subscribed space is the volume size. The value of this field will be equal to sum of eqliscsiVolumeSize field in volume mib.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeSpaceAllocate.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeSpaceAllocated
eqlStorageGroupStatusVolumeSpaceAllocate.description: The value of this object represents the sum of actual materialized pages for all volumes in the group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusFailbackSpace.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusFailbackSpace
eqlStorageGroupStatusFailbackSpace.description: This field represents the amount of space consumed by fail-back replicasets in this storage group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusThinProvFreeSpace.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusThinProvFreeSpace
eqlStorageGroupStatusThinProvFreeSpace.description: This field represents the amount of space available for Thin Provisioned Volumes in this storage group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusConnectionCount.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusConnectionCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusConnectionCount.description: This field gives the number of iSCSI connections that are currently connected to volumes in this group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapReserveSpaceFre.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapReserveSpaceFree
eqlStorageGroupStatusSnapReserveSpaceFre.description: This represents the total space still available for Snapshot usage.

eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveSpaceFre.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveSpaceFree
eqlStorageGroupStatusReplReserveSpaceFre.description: This represents the total space still available for Replica Snapshot usage.

eqlStorageGroupStatusGroupId.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusGroupId
eqlStorageGroupStatusGroupId.description: This represents an ID uniquely representing a group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumeCount.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumeCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumeCount.description: This field specifies the total number of volumes in this group, adjusted to remove volumes not typically visible such as synchronous replication standbys.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumesOnlin.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumesOnline
eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumesOnlin.description: This field specifies the total number of volumes available for iSCSI connections, excluding synchronous replication standbys.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumesInUse.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumesInUse
eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumesInUse.description: This field specifies the total number of volumes within the group that currently have active iSCSI connections excluding synchronous replication standbys.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumeSpaceS.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumeSpaceSubscribed
eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualVolumeSpaceS.description: This field specifies the total subscribed space for all volumes in the group. For a thin provisioned volume, subscribed space is the advertised space. For a regular volume, subscribed space is the volume size. The value of this field will be equal to sum of eqliscsiVolumeSize field in volume mib. This value is adjusted to exclude subscribed space for synchronous replication standby volumes.

eqlStorageGroupStatsTotalSpaceBorrowing.name: eqlStorageGroupStatsTotalSpaceBorrowing
eqlStorageGroupStatsTotalSpaceBorrowing.description: This field specifies the total amount of borrowing against other volume's free snapshot reserve and pool free space. This includes snapshots and recoverable volumes.

eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerCou.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerCou.description: This field specifies the total number of storage containers within the group.

eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVol.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVolumeCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVol.description: This field specifies the total number of volume resources that are being consumed within all storage containers.

eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerSna.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerSnapCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerSna.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshot resources that are being consumed within all storage containers.

eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVol.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVolumesOnline
eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVol.description: This field specifies the total number of online volume resources that are being consumed within all storage containers.

eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerSpa.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerSpaceReserved
eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerSpa.description: This field specifies the total amount of storage that is being consumed within all storage containers.

eqlStorageGroupStatusCompressedSpaceUsed.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusCompressedSpaceUsed
eqlStorageGroupStatusCompressedSpaceUsed.description: This field specifies the total amount of space in MB that is currently utilized for compressed pages. This is a dynamic value and cannot be set.

eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualSpaceSize.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualSpaceSize
eqlStorageGroupStatusVirtualSpaceSize.description: This field specifies the total amount of space in MB that would be utilized by compressed pages if there was no compression.

eqlStorageGroupStatusReplicationSnapCoun.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusReplicationSnapCount
eqlStorageGroupStatusReplicationSnapCoun.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshot resources that are being consumed for replication. This includes inbound replicas, and temporary snapshots used for in-progress outbound replication.

eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVol.name: eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVolumesBound
eqlStorageGroupStatusStorageContainerVol.description: This field specifies the total number of bound volume across all storage containers.

eqlStorageGroupSiteEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupSiteEntry
eqlStorageGroupSiteEntry.description: An entry (row) containing storage group site information.

eqlGroupSiteIndex.name: eqlGroupSiteIndex
eqlGroupSiteIndex.description: This field specifies the unique index used to identify a site.

eqlGroupSiteName.name: eqlGroupSiteName
eqlGroupSiteName.description: This field specifies the name of the site default site for the group.

eqlGroupSiteDescription.name: eqlGroupSiteDescription
eqlGroupSiteDescription.description: This field contains a description of the site. For example the phsyical address of the site. There is no default.

eqlGroupSiteContactEmail.name: eqlGroupSiteContactEmail
eqlGroupSiteContactEmail.description: This field specifies the email address of the Administrators responsible for this site.

eqlGroupSiteContactPhone.name: eqlGroupSiteContactPhone
eqlGroupSiteContactPhone.description: This field specifies the phone number of the Administrator responsible for this site.

eqlGroupSiteContactMobile.name: eqlGroupSiteContactMobile
eqlGroupSiteContactMobile.description: This field specifies the cell phone number of the Administrator responsible for this site.

eqlStorageGroupDnsServerTable.name: eqlStorageGroupDnsServerTable
eqlStorageGroupDnsServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group DNS Server Table TimeoutAll:600

eqlStorageGroupDnsServerEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupDnsServerEntry
eqlStorageGroupDnsServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group dns server information.

eqlGroupDnsServerIndex.name: eqlGroupDnsServerIndex
eqlGroupDnsServerIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the DNS server entry.

eqlGroupDnsServerIpAddress.name: eqlGroupDnsServerIpAddress
eqlGroupDnsServerIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupDnsServerInetAddressType.name: eqlGroupDnsServerInetAddressType
eqlGroupDnsServerInetAddressType.description: This field contains the IP address type for the DNS server.

eqlGroupDnsServerInetAddress.name: eqlGroupDnsServerInetAddress
eqlGroupDnsServerInetAddress.description: This field contains the IP address, in network byte order, for the DNS server.

eqlGroupDnsServerConfigState.name: eqlGroupDnsServerConfigState
eqlGroupDnsServerConfigState.description: This field denotes the transaction state of the eqlStorageGroupDnsServerTable.

eqlStorageGroupNtpServerTable.name: eqlStorageGroupNtpServerTable
eqlStorageGroupNtpServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group NTP Server Table

eqlStorageGroupNtpServerEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupNtpServerEntry
eqlStorageGroupNtpServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group ntp server information.

eqlGroupNtpServerIndex.name: eqlGroupNtpServerIndex
eqlGroupNtpServerIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the NTP server entry.

eqlGroupNtpServerIpAddress.name: eqlGroupNtpServerIpAddress
eqlGroupNtpServerIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupNtpServerPort.name: eqlGroupNtpServerPort
eqlGroupNtpServerPort.description: The listening port number of the ntp server.Default value implies well known ntp port number ( 123 ) assigned by the IANA.

eqlGroupNtpServerInetAddressType.name: eqlGroupNtpServerInetAddressType
eqlGroupNtpServerInetAddressType.description: This field contains the IP address type for the NTP server.

eqlGroupNtpServerInetAddress.name: eqlGroupNtpServerInetAddress
eqlGroupNtpServerInetAddress.description: This field contains the IP address, in network byte order, for the NTP server.

eqlStorageGroupChapServerTable.name: eqlStorageGroupChapServerTable
eqlStorageGroupChapServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group Chap Server Table

eqlStorageGroupChapServerEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupChapServerEntry
eqlStorageGroupChapServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing storage group chap server information.

eqlGroupChapServerIndex.name: eqlGroupChapServerIndex
eqlGroupChapServerIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the CHAP server entry.

eqlGroupChapServerIpAddress.name: eqlGroupChapServerIpAddress
eqlGroupChapServerIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupChapServerPort.name: eqlGroupChapServerPort
eqlGroupChapServerPort.description: The listening port number of chap server at the specified ipaddress. The default value of zero implies that the authentication request will be forwarded to the default radius port(port number 1812). The value of this object is irrelevant if eqlGroupChapServerInetAddress is the loopback ipaddress.

eqlGroupChapServerRADIUSSecret.name: eqlGroupChapServerRADIUSSecret
eqlGroupChapServerRADIUSSecret.description: This field contains the RADIUS secret for this client. It can be set but it returns a zero-length string upon read.

eqlGroupChapServerInetAddressType.name: eqlGroupChapServerInetAddressType
eqlGroupChapServerInetAddressType.description: This field contains the IP address type for the CHAP server.

eqlGroupChapServerInetAddress.name: eqlGroupChapServerInetAddress
eqlGroupChapServerInetAddress.description: This field contains the IP address, in network byte order, for the CHAP server.

eqlStorageGroupSMTPServerTable.name: eqlStorageGroupSMTPServerTable
eqlStorageGroupSMTPServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group SMTP Server Table

eqlStorageGroupSMTPServerEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupSMTPServerEntry
eqlStorageGroupSMTPServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group smtp sever information.

eqlGroupSMTPServerIndex.name: eqlGroupSMTPServerIndex
eqlGroupSMTPServerIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the SMTP server entry.

eqlGroupSMTPServerIpAddress.name: eqlGroupSMTPServerIpAddress
eqlGroupSMTPServerIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupSMTPServerPort.name: eqlGroupSMTPServerPort
eqlGroupSMTPServerPort.description: The listening port number of the SMTP server. The default value of zero implies that the server is listening on wellknown port number ( 25 ) for SMTP asssigned by the IANA.

eqlGroupSMTPServerInetAddressType.name: eqlGroupSMTPServerInetAddressType
eqlGroupSMTPServerInetAddressType.description: This field contains the IP address type for the SMTP server.

eqlGroupSMTPServerInetAddress.name: eqlGroupSMTPServerInetAddress
eqlGroupSMTPServerInetAddress.description: This field contains the IP address, in network byte order, for the SMTP server.

eqlStorageGroupSysLogServerTable.name: eqlStorageGroupSysLogServerTable
eqlStorageGroupSysLogServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group SysLog Server Table

eqlStorageGroupSysLogServerEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupSysLogServerEntry
eqlStorageGroupSysLogServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group syslog server info.

eqlGroupSysLogServerIndex.name: eqlGroupSysLogServerIndex
eqlGroupSysLogServerIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the syslog server entry.

eqlGroupSysLogServerIpAddress.name: eqlGroupSysLogServerIpAddress
eqlGroupSysLogServerIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupSysLogServerInetAddressType.name: eqlGroupSysLogServerInetAddressType
eqlGroupSysLogServerInetAddressType.description: This field contains the IP address type for the syslog server.

eqlGroupSysLogServerInetAddress.name: eqlGroupSysLogServerInetAddress
eqlGroupSysLogServerInetAddress.description: This field contains the IP address, in network byte order, for the syslog server.

eqlStorageGroupAlertEmailTable.name: eqlStorageGroupAlertEmailTable
eqlStorageGroupAlertEmailTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group Email Alert Table

eqlStorageGroupAlertEmailEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupAlertEmailEntry
eqlStorageGroupAlertEmailEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group alert email info.

eqlGroupAlertEmailIndex.name: eqlGroupAlertEmailIndex
eqlGroupAlertEmailIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the email user to alert.

eqlGroupAlertEmailAddress.name: eqlGroupAlertEmailAddress
eqlGroupAlertEmailAddress.description: This field specifies the email address of the Adminstrator targeted to recieve the email the email alerts.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountTable.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountTable
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group Administration account table. This table contains a collection of administration account records. It is indexed by group id and administration account record index.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountEntry
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountEntry.description: An entry (row) containing administration account settings.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountIndex.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountIndex
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountIndex.description: The index value that uniquely identifies the administration account record.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountRowStatus.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountRowStatus
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountRowStatus.description: This value is used to manage the conceptual row.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountName.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountName
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountName.description: EQL-SECONDARY-KEY The name of the administration account. This name must be used for user authentication.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPassword.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPassword
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPassword.description: An octet string containing the (crypt cipher) password for this account. If written, it changes the password for the account. If read, it returns a zero-length string.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountDescription.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountDescription
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountDescription.description: This field contains a description of the administration account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountType.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountType
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountType.description: This field specifies the type of account. The read-write account type allows the user to modify any group settings. The read-only account allows only read-only access to group configuration data. The default is read-write. Changing this value will come into affect only for new login of the user. Currently logged in sessions will not be affected.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountContact.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountContact
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountContact.description: This field contains the full name of the owner of this administration account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountEmail.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountEmail
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountEmail.description: This field specifies the email address of the owner of this administration account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPhone.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPhone
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPhone.description: This field specifies the phone number of the owner of this administration account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountMobile.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountMobile
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountMobile.description: This field specifies the cell phone number of the owner of this administration account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountStatus.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountStatus
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountStatus.description: This field represents the administration status of the account. Disabling the account will prevent the user from logging into CLI and GUI. Currently logged-in sessions will not be affected.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountCliFlags.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountCliFlags
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountCliFlags.description: This field specifies the set of configuration flags used by the CLI. These flags allow the administrator to save CLI configuration settings between the CLI sessions. The meaning of individual bits is not defined yet. TBD

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountGuiFlags.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountGuiFlags
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountGuiFlags.description: This field specifies the set of configuration flags used by the GUI. These flags allow the administrator to save GUI configuration settings between the GUI sessions. The meaning of individual bits is not defined yet. TBD

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPollInterval.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPollInterval
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPollInterval.description: The value of this field specifies how often the group configuration data must be repolled by the GUI. This value is expressed in seconds. The minimum is 5 seconds; the maximum is 1 hour. The default is 30 seconds.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountAuthType.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountAuthType
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountAuthType.description: This field represents the type of authentication for the administrator. Note that RADIUS/LDAP type users will only appear in the table after a successful login.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountRecentLogin.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountRecentLogin
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountRecentLogin.description: This field represents a timestamp of the most recent time this admin account has logged in. Currently only applies to radius auth type users.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountClass.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountClass
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountClass.description: This field contains the contents of the class attribute received in the RADIUS Access-Request and must be reflected in the RADIUS Accounting-Request if accounting is enabled.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPrivilege.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPrivilege
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountPrivilege.description: This field specifies the privilege level of the account. The default is global-admin. global-admin grants full access to the administrator. pool-admin designates the administrator to have access only to one or more pools, and does not have access to global and group-level administrator. volume-admin designates the administrator to have access to specific volumes within specific storage pools.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSnmpKey.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSnmpKey
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSnmpKey.description: This field contain part of the SNMP key for this account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSnmpKey2.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSnmpKey2
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSnmpKey2.description: This field contain part of the SNMP second key for this account.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountCHAPPassword.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountCHAPPassword
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountCHAPPassword.description: An octet string containing the (cleartext) password for this account. If written, it changes the password for the account. If read, it returns a zero-length string.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountKey.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountKey
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountKey.description: A value to uniquely identify this account. The MIB attribute eqliscsiVolumeAdminAccountKey uses this value to associate a volume with an account. No two accounts can have the same value.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountAdGroupName.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountAdGroupName
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountAdGroupName.description: The name of the Active Directory group, valid only when auth type is LDAP. Same as cn attribute of the AD group.

eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSNMPPrivProt.name: eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSNMPPrivProt
eqlStorageGroupAdminAccountSNMPPrivProt.description: An enum field used by the Agent to determine which privacy protocol is used to encrypt external SNMP messages for this user.

eqlStorageGroupiSNSServerTable.name: eqlStorageGroupiSNSServerTable
eqlStorageGroupiSNSServerTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Storage Group iSNS Server Table

eqlStorageGroupiSNSServerEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupiSNSServerEntry
eqlStorageGroupiSNSServerEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group iSNS server information.

eqlGroupiSNSServerIndex.name: eqlGroupiSNSServerIndex
eqlGroupiSNSServerIndex.description: This field specifies an index that uniquely identifies the iSNS server entry.

eqlGroupiSNSServerIpAddress.name: eqlGroupiSNSServerIpAddress
eqlGroupiSNSServerIpAddress.description: This field is deprecated and will be unsupported in the next release.

eqlGroupiSNSServerPort.name: eqlGroupiSNSServerPort
eqlGroupiSNSServerPort.description: Indicates the port the iSNS server is accepting iSNSP messages on, generally the iSNS well known port.The well known port for iSNSP is 3205. The default value implies to use well known port.

eqlGroupiSNSServerInetAddressType.name: eqlGroupiSNSServerInetAddressType
eqlGroupiSNSServerInetAddressType.description: This field contains the IP address type for the iSNS server.

eqlGroupiSNSServerInetAddress.name: eqlGroupiSNSServerInetAddress
eqlGroupiSNSServerInetAddress.description: This field contains the IP address, in network byte order, for the iSNS server.

eqlGroupCompatibilityEntry.name: eqlGroupCompatibilityEntry
eqlGroupCompatibilityEntry.description: An entry (row) containing group compatibility information.

eqlGroupCurrentCompLevel.name: eqlGroupCurrentCompLevel
eqlGroupCurrentCompLevel.description: This field represents the current compatibility level of the group.

eqlStorageGroupCollectionTable.name: eqlStorageGroupCollectionTable
eqlStorageGroupCollectionTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Group Collection Table. This table maintains overall number of volume collections and snap collection in a group.

eqlStorageGroupCollectionEntry.name: eqlStorageGroupCollectionEntry
eqlStorageGroupCollectionEntry.description: An entry (row) containing volume/snap collections information in a group.

eqlGrpNoofVolCollections.name: eqlGrpNoofVolCollections
eqlGrpNoofVolCollections.description: This field specifies the total number of volume collections in the group ie number of rows in eqliscsiVolCollectionTable.

eqlGrpNoofSnapCollections.name: eqlGrpNoofSnapCollections
eqlGrpNoofSnapCollections.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshot collections in the group ie number of rows in eqliscsiSnapCollectionTable.

eqlGrpNoofOrphanSnapCollections.name: eqlGrpNoofOrphanSnapCollections
eqlGrpNoofOrphanSnapCollections.description: This field specifies the total number of snapshot collections in the group that dont have a corresponding volume set ie number of rows in eqliscsiSnapCollectionTable with eqliscsiSnapCollectionVolIndex set to zero.

eqlRADIUSTable.name: eqlRADIUSTable
eqlRADIUSTable.description: EqualLogic-Persistent Group RADIUS Configuration Table. This table maintains the configuration for the RADIUS implementation.

eqlRADIUSEntry.name: eqlRADIUSEntry
eqlRADIUSEntry.description: An entry (row) containing RADIUS information in a group.

eqlRADIUSSecret.name: eqlRADIUSSecret
eqlRADIUSSecret.description: This field contains the RADIUS secret for this client. It can be set but it returns a zero-length string upon read.

eqlRADIUSLoginAuthEnable.name: eqlRADIUSLoginAuthEnable
eqlRADIUSLoginAuthEnable.description: This field enables RADIUS login authentication.

eqlRADIUSAuthRecvTimeout.name: eqlRADIUSAuthRecvTimeout
